Project No: 0004 (Improved Version 0003 Project folder)
Project Name: Creating Multiple Apps in One Django Project (Using urls.py inside each app)

ðŸ“Œ Step 1: Create the Django Project
django-admin startproject HIETECH

ðŸ“Œ Step 2: Enter into the Project Directory
cd HIETECH

ðŸ“Œ Step 3: Create Django Applications
py manage.py startapp Students
py manage.py startapp Fees
py manage.py startapp Courses


Add them to HIETECH/settings.py:

INSTALLED_APPS = [
    'django.contrib.admin',
    'django.contrib.auth',
    'django.contrib.contenttypes',
    'django.contrib.sessions',
    'django.contrib.messages',
    'django.contrib.staticfiles',
    'Students',
    'Fees',
    'Courses',
]

ðŸ“Œ Step 4: Define View Functions
Students/views.py
from django.shortcuts import HttpResponse

def student_view1(request):
    return HttpResponse('<h1>Hello, you are in the Students section (view1)</h1>')

def student_view2(request):
    return HttpResponse('<h1>Hello, you are in the Students section (view2)</h1>')

Fees/views.py
from django.shortcuts import HttpResponse

def fees_view(request):
    return HttpResponse('<h1>Hello, you are in the Fees section</h1>')

Courses/views.py
from django.shortcuts import HttpResponse

def course_view(request):
    return HttpResponse('<h1>Hello, you are in the Courses section</h1>')

ðŸ“Œ Step 5: Create urls.py inside each app
Students/urls.py
from django.urls import path
from . import views

urlpatterns = [
    path('view1/', views.student_view1, name="student_view1"),
    path('view2/', views.student_view2, name="student_view2"),
]

Fees/urls.py
from django.urls import path
from . import views

urlpatterns = [
    path('', views.fees_view, name="fees_view"),
]

Courses/urls.py
from django.urls import path
from . import views

urlpatterns = [
    path('', views.course_view, name="course_view"),
]

ðŸ“Œ Step 6: Configure Project-Level urls.py
HIETECH/urls.py
from django.contrib import admin
from django.urls import path, include

urlpatterns = [
    path('admin/', admin.site.urls),

    # Include app-level urls
    path('students/', include('Students.urls')),
    path('fees/', include('Fees.urls')),
    path('courses/', include('Courses.urls')),
]

ðŸ“Œ Step 7: Run Development Server
py manage.py runserver

ðŸ“Œ Step 8: Test URLs

Students App:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/students/view1/
http://127.0.0.1:8000/students/view2/

Fees App:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/fees/

Courses App:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/courses/

âœ… Advantages of this structure:
Keeps each app self-contained.
Easier to maintain as the project grows.
No conflicts with multiple views.py.
Cleaner project-level urls.py.